values: and OMFG you guys! I won an LJ auction for an authentic Spank sweater/mini dress/tunic last week. I am seriously so obsessed with those girls..I would prob. pay $10 for a baseball card that they held in their hands. It would be so rad to be able to travel to Japan and party with them! I'll bet they always have a lot of fun. Here's a picture from the seller ( swan_princess ). I shall re-take some once it arrives! I need new shoes to wear with it lol..I think they'd look great with fishnets, legwarmers, my leather jacket..and the black rocking horse shoes I've been wanting for forever!! Wee outfitz! I can't wait to see how it fits! I'm hoping I can pass it as a mini..if not I'll buy a ruffley skirt to pair it with! Yay! Ooz, I wonder who made it! I want to order more stuff (including like 100 bows) but am currently too poor to hire shopping services and such just for it to get to me from Japan >_<. Maybe someday! Yep..Just wanted to share my excitement with you =0DDDDDDDD Oh! and I bought a cute Barbie and The Rockers top from applenoggin the other week. Wee new clothes I can't buy anything for a while ::tear:: until I pay off Etsy..but I'll show you guys some more cute stuff I bought last month a lil' later!

5/20/08 These past few days I've been really bad about sewing and getting things done to sell. I've just been so out of it and haven't felt like doing anything. I'm usually good for a week or two and then I just feel really down and out for a while. I started a Rainbow Brite wallet as well as a RB t-shirt that I'll be listing on LJ soon. I also want to get a tote or two done. I'm def. making one out of the smiley food dabric I have but somone already has first dibs on that one! Yesterday Joey and I went to the mall since he wanted to buy some new clothes. I really didn't feel like going but it was nice to get out of the house for once and go somewhere besides Joanne fabrics or the post office! There was a sale on t-shirts at Hot Topic..I wanted the one that said "I'm a Doll" on it but then I found the Friday the 13th shirt I've been wanting for forever on sale in a size small hidden! I saw an xl and was like dammmn and then I dug a bit and found one! There were 2 really hot Elvira tops too but they were a bit too short for my taste. There was a Fresh Prince one too that fit real good lol. Joey said I could get 2 of them but I didn't want to be greedy and just got the Friday the 13th top. Yayyy! I used to never allow him to spend money on me..but hey..I was at the mall and broke so I was like oooh you should buy me this! lol. While he was shopping I wandered into Claire's. I had 8 bucks left on my credit card so I bought this cute kitten purse meant for little girls to throw over their shoulder. I'm guna use it as a purse necklace, yay! Lately my bulky shoulder purses have been a major annoyance so I bought a cute cuipcake clutch the other week and that kitten thing. I saw the cutest little sparkly unicorn earrings there.. as well as 2 reallllly cute kitten pouches but I was out of monies =<. I found Joey and asked him if he'd like to get me the $4 earrings HEHE..so he did..and then he saw me gazing at a kitten pouch so he said get that too..and I was trying to decide between two of them and he grabbed them both and got me them WEE presents! He bought me some food at Panda Express tooz..mmm so good! I felt so spoiled..yay! My friend Geneve came over to do me and my parents' hair. I haven't gotten a dye/cut job in almost 3 months >_<..I reallly needed it! Turns out the Gwar show is already coming up this Friday so we're going to go. Hurray! ..Yesterday a boutique owner contacted me about a wholesale order for my cupcake hair bows and clip packs..so we'll see how that goes! It would be my first wholesale order...I hope she wants 800 of them lol. I'm pretty sleepy.I should really be sewing to save up for my etsy bill..but I'm on the internetz instead >_0. k!

I'm a dumbass and neglected my Etsy bill for far too long so now my listing ability is currently suspended until I pay the $90 (Yeah, I haven't paid it in a LONG time I know, I totally suck and have busy buying other things on Etsy instead ::smacks head::!). I'll be listing all of my updates in this post until I am able to get my bill situated. It will prob. be around 2 weeks or so >_<. Here is my shop: http://www.etsy.com/shop.php?user_id=5262757

"People are still able to purchase through my shop as usual. Unfortunately I'm unable to delete my items in the shop so if you aren't an Etsy member I'll be unable to sell those things to you. This seriously made my ENTIRE week. I created a custom bag for the loveliest lady located in the UK. It was a re-make of another bag, only I made it messenger style since she's a busy momma! She was so incredibly sweet during the entire transaction. I received this message and feedback just now, and I don't think I've ever been so touched! Sometimes I really don't think my stuff is that good and have doubts about what others think, but this really put a huge smile on my face! It makes me feel so good when I hear good feedback from customers. It makes me feel even better when people are so happy with their purchases that they return! Nothing could ever top that ^.^ "Nikki, Received the amazing bag today. I hope the feedback says it all but I just wanted to say I think you are HUGELY TALENTED - I cannot believe you are only 19...your work is equisite. I wish you all the very best with your future sales and again - THANK YOU THANK YOU THANK YOU for creating my very favorite birthday present this year! Big hugs Katie" "OMG!!!!!!! Nikki...the tote is even nicer in person and I didn't think that was possible. I absolutely adore it. Thank you so very much for making such an amazing bag. To potential buyers.....this lady is seriously tallented. The stitching on this bag is immaculate and is so extremely well made. I think this has to be the best item I have bought on Etsy so far - from the nicest of sellers who bent over backwards to make this very special bag for me. Thank you Nikki!!!"

I just went to photobucket and on the main page they have a link to the most popualr searches..well "scene" is one of them. (I also love how "juno" is one of them??)OMG this is hilarious! Why would someone even categorize their picture into that? LAME-OS extreme! Scene queenz or even worse, wannabe scene queenz make me want to punch people =0D. and what's up with the rediculous eye liner? I love me some liner but these people look like they were pranked when looking through binoculars..ya know what I meanz? Lets take a look shall we?!
OMG like I'm SO fucking scene bitches. I absolutely love taking pictures from different angles..that all look the same. Scene! I wear black because I hate the world. I hear it's like, totally scene to hate the world. I cover one eye to block out half the people that I see. Scene! I like totally get my fashion advice from the Hot Topic homepage. Scene forever! I am so fucking mysterious with my magical lion hair This is my personal favorite. Yeah, she looks so intimidating doesn't she? AHAHAH! Check out the photoshopz knuckle tattooz! Wait, I'm queen right? I look ok, right? GUYS! Oh yeah, they're cool! Scene-core dude..SCENE-CORE! What the fuck does that even mean. Photoshopz for life! ? No makeup One of their use names is xxPunkxHardcorexEmoxx HAHAHA..Yea because those are totally similar. Or falloutboy_vamp girl..HAHAHA! Some of the girls I saw are actually pretty cute/hot, but seriously...I fucking hate this whole "scene" thing. It is so lame. Ok that's enough I can't look at any more. Well that was fun!

I have been neglecting my Etsy fees for the past month or two and owe 50 something dollars x_x. I need to get that taken care of asap. Monday night Joey took me out on a date =0D. We went to Stake and Shake (MM!) for dinner and then to a movie. We saw Juno. Frankly, I wasn't too pleased with it. I mean, it was good for an indie movie..but I thought (especially in the beginning) that they tried to make Juno and her girlfriend sound extremely too witty. It seemed like someone sat for hours just writing the phone conversation..It just didn't sound natural and too forced then and throughout the movie. I saw it hoping that it would have a bit more comedy even though it was about a serious thing..Joey and I prob. went to see it mostly because the kid from Superbad was in it honestly haha. Oh well, at least it was his treat because I never go to the theater at $10 a pop! I just wait until I can get them free with MVP at hollywood video =0D. I made an exception for Blades of Glory though and saw that when it came out..Right now I'm excited for when Sweeney and Todd is free with MVP. Speaking of Sweeney, Johnny Depp was in Crown Point the other week (and prob. still is) shooting some movie. Four years ago I would have jogged hours to hide in the bushes and stalk him. I don't have that little girl crush on him anymore, I just respect him as an amazing actor. I started a cute purse using the sweet treats fabric..I want to use gold d-rings on it but ran out so I'll have to wait until I get the ones I ordered off Etsy to finish =/. Hmmm..I think that's it. I think I'll go lurk the MAC community..I haven't checked up on anything for over a month. I really want to get some heatherette stuff though so hopefully there's swatches galore by now!
